<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: ROCKWELL - DISASSEMBLY - AXLE UNIVERSAL JOINT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>AXLE UNIVERSAL JOINT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the universal joint and drive shaft assembly straight from the carrier and housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200815">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200815" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200815.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Removing Universal Joint and Drive Shaft Axle Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil seal from the outer drive shaft. Discard the seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If required, remove the inner drive shaft oil seal, thrust washer and bushing from the axle
                housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200816">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200816" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200816.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Axle Housing Seal Washer Bushing and Adapter Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. OIL SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. ADAPTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BUSHING</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Some axles have the inner drive shaft bushing installed in the bushing adapter. The adapter
                        MUST NOT be removed from the housing (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0200816">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Rockwell Front Driving Axles have two different universal joint designs:</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Wing Bearing Yokes</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Round Bearing Yokes</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>The correct disassembly procedures for each design of yoke follow:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wing Bearing Yokes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200817">Figure 17</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200817" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200817.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Wing Bearing Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the eight cross assembly capscrews (four capscrews and nuts for each yoke).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">Do not</emph>
                    disassemble the cross assembly. If the cross assembly needs service, replace it with a new assembly.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Round Bearing Yokes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200818">Figure 18</hotlnk>)
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200818" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200818.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Round Bearing Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the snap rings from the two ears in each yoke.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Put the joint assembly in an open vise with one yoke in a horizontal position and the
                    other yoke against the top of the vise jaws.
                    <emph type="bold">Do not</emph>
                    tighten the vise.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With a soft mallet, hit the upper ear of the vertical yoke several times to release the
                    upper needle bearing and cap. Be careful that you do not damage the polished surface of the bearing
                    cap during removal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200819">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200819" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200819.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Releasing Bearing and Cap</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn the yoke upside down and remove the needle bearing and retainer on the opposite ear
                    following the procedure described above.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the yoke by carefully working it off the arms of the cross (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200820">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200820" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200820.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 20. Removing Universal Joint Cross from Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">To complete the disassembly, hold the remaining arms in a vertical position and set the
                    cross arms on top of the open vise. Repeat Steps C through E.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
